You need to create a &quot;Run/Debug Configuration&quot; (Menu &quot;Run&quot; -&gt; &quot;Edit Configurations...&quot;).

About halfway down in the configuration panel is an entry &quot;Redirect input from&quot; with a checkbox before it. After selecting the checkbox you can select the file &quot;tinyT.txt&quot;.

&quot;tinyW.txt&quot; has to be entered into the field &quot;Program arguments&quot;

---
Some time after writing this answer the Run/Debug configuration dialog has change. In 2023 if you want to redirect the input from some file you need to select &quot;Modify Options&quot; and then &quot;Redirect Input&quot;

Please make sure, that DoctorDetailsActivity is added to your **Manifest.xml** file. It should be present in the **application** section:

    &lt;application
        &lt;activity
            android:name=&quot;.DoctorDetailsActivity&quot;
            android:exported=&quot;false&quot;
        &lt;/activity&gt;
    &lt;/application&gt;

Your DoctorDetailsActivity activity is apparently in the main branch of your project, so above declaration is fine. But if you would like to add activities that are in some subdirectories (i.e. in dir1/dir2/DoctorDetailsActivity), just add it like this:

    &lt;application
        &lt;activity
            android:name=&quot;.dir1.dir2.DoctorDetailsActivity&quot;
            android:exported=&quot;false&quot;
        &lt;/activity&gt;
    &lt;/application&gt;


I set **exported** as false as you obviously do not want this activity to be started from outside your app - you assume that Bundle is non-empty, and there is some Title key with some non-empty value present - you do not consider empty string.

Another thing is that you missed setting OnClickListener for the **surgeon** variable in FindDoctorActivity. Instead you overwrite familyphysician&#39; OnClickListener (probably copy+pate mistake). With that, clicking on surgeon will have no effect, as no OnClickListener is defined - you will stay on FindDoctorActivity. If you haven&#39;t added DoctorDetailsActivity to your manifest, attempt to click all other doctors will crash your app.

